adClicks.name: adClicks
adClicks.comment: Total number of times users have clicked on an ad.

adCost.name: adCost
adCost.comment: The total amount you paid for your ads. Its currency is the one you set in the AdWords account.

adwordsAdGroupID.name: adwordsAdGroupID
adwordsAdGroupID.comment: The unique identification number of your Google Ads ad group.

bounces.name: bounces
bounces.comment: The total number of single page (or single interaction hit) sessions for the property

campaign.name: campaign
campaign.comment: The names of your Google Ads campaigns or custom campaigns that you have manually tagged with the utm_campaign parameter; or any of your Campaign Manager 360 or Search Ads 360 campaigns if you have linked those Google Marketing Platform advertising accounts to Analytics.

channelGrouping.name: channelGrouping
channelGrouping.comment: The Channel Group associated with an end user's session for this View (defined by the View's Channel Groupings)

impressions.name: impressions
impressions.comment: The number of views of an internal promotion.

pageviews.name: pageviews
pageviews.comment: The total number of pages viewed. Repeated views of a single page are counted.

sessionDuration.name: sessionDuration
sessionDuration.comment: Total duration (in seconds) of users' sessions

sessions.name: sessions
sessions.comment: Total number of Sessions within the date range. A session is the period time a user is actively engaged with your website, app, etc. All usage data (Screen Views, Events, Ecommerce, etc.) is associated with a session.

source.name: source
source.comment: Source shows where users were before seeing your content, such as a search engine or another website. This dimension also includes the custom values you define for source and medium.

sourceMedium.name: sourceMedium
sourceMedium.comment: Source shows where users were before seeing your content, such as a search engine or another website. Medium shows how users arrived at your content, such as "organic" for unpaid search traffic and "(none)" for direct traffic. This dimension also includes the custom values you define for source and medium

transactionRevenue.name: transactionRevenue
transactionRevenue.comment: The total sale revenue (excluding shipping and tax) of the transaction

transactions.name: transactions
transactions.comment: The total number of completed purchases on your site.

configName.name: configName
configName.comment: Individual page, profile, ads account or account for the data source.

frequency.name: frequency
frequency.comment: The average number of times each person saw your ad.

account_id.name: account_id
account_id.comment: The ID number of your ad account, which groups your advertising activity. Your ad account includes your campaigns, ads, and billing.

ad_id.name: ad_id
ad_id.comment: Unique ID of the ad being viewed in reporting

ad_name.name: ad_name
ad_name.comment: The name of the ad you're viewing in reporting.

adset_id.name: adset_id
adset_id.comment: The unique ID of the ad set you're viewing in reporting. An ad set is a group of ads that share the same budget, schedule, delivery optimization and targeting. This column does not apply to campaigns, only ad sets and ads.

adset_name.name: adset_name
adset_name.comment: The name of the ad set you're viewing in reporting. An ad set is a group of ads that share the same budget, schedule, delivery optimization and targeting.

body.name: body
body.comment: The text displayed in the body of your ad. This column does not apply to campaigns or ad sets, only ads.

campaign_id.name: campaign_id
campaign_id.comment: The unique ID number of the ad campaign you're viewing in reporting. Your campaign contains ad sets and ads.

campaign_name.name: campaign_name
campaign_name.comment: The name of the ad campaign you're viewing in reporting. Your campaign contains ad sets and ads.

clicks.name: clicks
clicks.comment: The number of clicks on your ads.

date.name: date
date.comment: The dimension that determines how date-based data in a chart is handled (the time dimension).

impressions.name: impressions
impressions.comment: The number of times your ads were on screen.

reach.name: reach
reach.comment: The number of people who saw your ads at least once. Reach is different from impressions, which may include multiple views of your ads by the same people.

spend.name: spend
spend.comment: The estimated total amount of money you've spent on your campaign, ad set or ad during its schedule.
